compilation of environmental effect utilities.
by: art.nugraha

DATABASE:

[1] mu.dat <-- effective mass data
	
	how to use:
	mu(n,m,i,1) <-- electron mass
	mu(n,m,i,2) <-- hole mass
	mu(n,m,i,3) <-- electron-hole mass
		
[2] eii.dat <-- eii, lk, dt, and theta data

	how to use:
	Eii(n,m,i,nkapp,1) <-- eii
	Eii(n,m,i,nkapp,2) <-- lk
	dttheta(n,m,1) <-- dt
	dttheta(n,m,2) <-- theta

FORTRAN CODES:

[1] envrout.f90 <-- database module and useful "find" subroutines

	eiimudt summarizes the eiimudt database

[2] conkapeii.f90 <-- check eii calculation from optimized kappa data

	this will give an original input of experimental eii for
	any samples
